GREP COMMAND 
* it is used to search pattern/string in a file
* to check the wheather the error or not .
* grep "devan" onefile
* l -> shows the file name 
* -h -> shows the word without the file name 
* -n -> shows the line along with the line numbers.
* -c -> count the number of the line which is present over there .
* -v -> print all the files instaed of the given word.
* grep "o$" * to find the starting pattern 
* grep "^i" to find the ending pattern.
